Key Match Events: Shubman Gill helped India past the 100 run mark with a boundary in the 10th over.
Yashasvi Jaiswal finished things off in style as he hits a boundary of Muzarbani to help team India secure a 10 wicket victory in Harare.
Skipper Shubman Gill helped India score 182/4 in 20 overs while Zimbabwe managed 159/6 in their 20 overs.
Pre-Game Insights: Ruturaj Gaikwad leads the tournament in runs with 133 at an average of 66.50.
Abhishek Sharma scored 100 in his second match but didn't do well in the other two, including a duck in his first.
Skipper Gill has 99 runs so far.
Post-Match Reflections: Yashasvi Jaiswal is the man of the match
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at Harare Sports Stadium.
